From e862168cd7243054e557168005991504125e4b9b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Harish Rachakonda <rachakon@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 31 Jul 2025 21:46:16 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:CP:hostapd: ATF: Build vendor NL to send configs

Add QCA vendor command and attributes for Airtime Fairness (ATF)
offload operations. This command enables configuration and control of ATF
features, which aim to managing airtime distribution across various
entities such as SSIDs, SSID groups, peers, and access categories.

This interface is intended for use to dynamically manage airtime
distribution based on scheduling policy (if configured) across various
entities such as SSIDs, SSID groups, peers, and access categories.

Introduced SSID group NL attribute to send airtime configurations.
  Includes:
  - Group index
  - Group-level airtime
  - Group scheduling policy
  - Configured/unconfigured peers
  - unconfigured peers airtime

Added WMM AC NL attribute to convey per-group WMM AC airtime
configurations.

Implemented peer NL attribute to support:
  - Full or partial peer updates
  - Peer count and continuation flag
  - Per-peer airtime, MAC address, configuration status, and group ID

Signed-off-by: Harish Rachakonda <rachakon@qti.qualcomm.com>
